#, no-wrap
msgid "Mapping Claims and Assertions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/identity-broker/mappers.adoc:7
#, no-wrap
msgid "You can import the SAML and OpenID Connect metadata provided by the external IDP you are authenticating with into the environment\n"
"of the realm.  This allows you to extract user profile metadata and other information so that you can make it available to your\n"
"applications.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/identity-broker/mappers.adoc:11
#, no-wrap
msgid "Each new user that logs into your realm via an external identity provider will have an entry for it created in the local\n"
"{project_name} database.  The act of importing metadata from the SAML or OIDC assertions and claims will create this data\n"
"with the local realm database.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/identity-broker/mappers.adoc:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you click on an identity provider listed in the `Identity Providers` page for your realm, you will be brought to the IDPs\n"
"`Settings` tab.  On this page is also a `Mappers` tab.  Click on that tab to start mapping your incoming IDP metadata.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/identity-broker/mappers.adoc:16
#, no-wrap
msgid "image:{project_images}/identity-provider-mappers.png[]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/identity-broker/mappers.adoc:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "There is a `Create` button on this page.\n"
"Clicking on this create button allows you to create a broker mapper.\n"
"Broker mappers can import SAML attributes or OIDC ID/Access token claims into user attributes and user role mappings.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/identity-broker/mappers.adoc:22
#, no-wrap
msgid "image:{project_images}/identity-provider-mapper.png[]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/identity-broker/mappers.adoc:25
#, no-wrap
msgid "Select a mapper from the `Mapper Type` list.  Hover over the tooltip to see a description of what the mapper does.  The\n"
"tooltips also describe what configuration information you need to enter. Click `Save` and your new mapper will be added.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/identity-broker/mappers.adoc:28
#, no-wrap
msgid "For JSON based claims, you can use dot notation for nesting and square brackets to access array fields by index.\n"
"For example 'contact.address[0].country'.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/identity-broker/mappers.adoc:30
#, no-wrap
msgid "To investigate the structure of user profile JSON data provided by social providers you can enable the `DEBUG` level logger `org.keycloak.social.user_profile_dump`.\n"
"This is done in the server's app-server configuration file (domain.xml or standalone.xml).\n"
msgstr ""

